1
00:00:00,667 --> 00:00:02,433
<i> You said that he was okay!</i>

2
00:00:02,567 --> 00:00:04,933
<i>You told us that
he was coming home to us!</i>

3
00:00:05,067 --> 00:00:06,700
<i> You lied!</i>

4
00:00:06,833 --> 00:00:10,367
<i>I don't want to see you
and your brothers here!</i>

5
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:12,467
<i> Leave!</i>

6
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:14,733
<i>- You're so stupid, Martin!
- You want to get hurt?</i>

7
00:00:14,867 --> 00:00:16,267
<i>- Here!
- [BLOW LANDS]</i>

8
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:18,000
[GRUNTS]

9
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:19,333
<i> Instead of punishing yourself,</i>

10
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:21,733
<i>give Leon's death the
dignity and justice it deserves!</i>

11
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:23,433
<i> That's the Martin Leon knew!</i>

12
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:26,033
<i>Until what happened
here gets resolved...</i>

13
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:28,100
<i> the hotel will remain closed.</i>

14
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:30,900
<i> Kiko is the key to this case.</i>

15
00:00:31,033 --> 00:00:31,733
<i> Ma.</i>

16
00:00:31,867 --> 00:00:33,867
<i> We heard Kiko is awake.</i>

17
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,667
<i> Can we talk to him now?</i>

18
00:00:36,367 --> 00:00:37,667
- [FLESH SQUELCHES]
- [GRUNTS]

19
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:39,033
<i> Leon!</i>

20
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,500
<i>- Kiko, run!
- [GRUNTS]</i>

21
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:43,100
<i>He stabbed him
again and again, sir.</i>

22
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:44,400
<i> There was so much blood.</i>

23
00:00:45,133 --> 00:00:46,700
<i> Who did this, Kiko?</i>

24
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:48,067
<i> Sandro.</i>

25
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,667
<i> Sandro Soliman.</i>

26
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,000
<i> He's alive?</i>

27
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:52,333
<i> He's alive.</i>

28
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:55,233
Sandro Soliman?

29
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:57,133
Is he sure?

30
00:00:58,633 --> 00:01:00,433
That's Kiko's statement.

31
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:02,600
That was the last thing
Leon said to him.

32
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:07,000
He's Juan's father.

33
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,500
Juan?

34
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:14,067
The body they found
in Leon's car?

35
00:01:14,967 --> 00:01:16,333
My son was killed

36
00:01:16,467 --> 00:01:19,533
because Juan's body
was found in his car?

37
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,033
That's a possibility.

38
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:24,033
Until we catch Sandro,

39
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:27,033
we won't know for sure.

40
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,933
All we know is

41
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:31,767
Kiko said Sandro's
looking for a map.

42
00:01:33,567 --> 00:01:34,700
But, sir...

43
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:38,067
How did Sandro get into
the hotel property?

44
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:41,433
If he worked
with Mr. Fernandez before,

45
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:44,133
he might know ways
to get in and out of the hotel.

46
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,800
If Sandro is still alive,

47
00:01:47,933 --> 00:01:49,533
that means he killed dad.

48
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,633
And, Sir Henri,

49
00:01:52,433 --> 00:01:54,333
Andy and Sandro
could be working together.

50
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:56,100
My gut's telling me it's him!

51
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:58,667
Luna!

52
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,933
No, let her be.

53
00:02:01,067 --> 00:02:01,933
[FRIDA SIGHS SHARPLY]

54
00:02:02,067 --> 00:02:09,133
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,033
[MARTIN] A little bit higher.

56
00:03:03,167 --> 00:03:04,533
Make sure it's hidden.

57
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:08,467
Have you fixed the
routers and everything needed

58
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,733
for the cameras'
wireless connection?

59
00:03:10,867 --> 00:03:12,400
[TECHNICIAN] Yes, sir.

60
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:14,167
Okay.

61
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:18,367
Are they waterproof
in case it rains?

62
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:19,400
Yeah.

63
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:22,867
Have you spoken to Luna?

64
00:03:24,067 --> 00:03:25,700
Not yet.

65
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:27,967
You know, just be patient.

66
00:03:28,867 --> 00:03:31,467
Aunt Frida was furious.
Give them some space.

67
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:34,300
I don't think that's it.

68
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:41,100
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:03:41,233 --> 00:03:43,267
This is where we found them.

70
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,367
This is where
Sandro attacked them.

71
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:52,700
Did he kill Leon
out of revenge?

72
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:54,700
It's possible.

73
00:03:56,467 --> 00:03:57,867
Did we make a mistake?

74
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:01,033
Were we wrong to think

75
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:03,767
Andy killed Papa
and Uncle Federico?

76
00:04:05,033 --> 00:04:07,200
If Sandro is alive,

77
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:09,367
and looking for the map,

78
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:11,800
and he killed Leon,

79
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:15,033
then it's possible he killed
Papa and Federico, too.

80
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:17,933
Are you saying we
were wrong about Andy?

81
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:21,633
We blamed everything
on him.

82
00:04:21,767 --> 00:04:22,733
To be honest...

83
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:25,533
I don't know anymore.

84
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:27,000
[MARTIN SIGHS]

85
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:30,333
They could be working together
to find the treasure.

86
00:04:32,133 --> 00:04:33,767
What matters now is,

87
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:37,167
whether they're
conspiring or not,

88
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:39,500
they will both rot in jail.

89
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:42,533
We will make sure
of that, Martin.

90
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:49,200
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,733
[FRIDA BREATHES HEAVILY]

92
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:53,767
Justin!

93
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:57,600
Why do you seem
to know so much?

94
00:04:58,367 --> 00:05:01,033
What are you not telling me?

95
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:03,300
First, you said it was Andy.

96
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:07,433
Now, you're saying
Sandro killed your father?

97
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:10,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

98
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:11,933
Justin,

99
00:05:13,267 --> 00:05:16,033
did I fail you
as a mother?

100
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:17,233
No, Mom.

101
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:18,833
Don't say that.

102
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,500
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

103
00:05:21,633 --> 00:05:26,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

104
00:05:26,233 --> 00:05:28,833
Sandro was a contractor
for Uncle Mike.

105
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:32,367
We believe he's working
with Andy.

106
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:33,933
They are looking for
a hidden treasure

107
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,533
at Hotel 88.

108
00:05:35,667 --> 00:05:36,967
What?

109
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:37,700
Treasure?

110
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:41,067
- Mom.
- [EXHALES]

111
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,500
Mom,
I know it's hard to believe.

112
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,000
But we believe
that's the real reason

113
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:47,667
why Andy wants to
become a partner.

114
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:52,700
Juan's body being found
in Leon's car

115
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:54,300
was a set-up.

116
00:06:00,867 --> 00:06:02,400
[KNOCKING]

117
00:06:16,633 --> 00:06:19,000
- I'll take that.
- Thank you.

118
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:24,033
- My deepest condolences.
- Thank you.

119
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:29,433
Our deepest condolences
for your loss.

120
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:31,700
Thank you.

121
00:06:32,633 --> 00:06:34,100
We'll give you two
some privacy.

122
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:35,867
Bro.

123
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,033
Go ahead, sweetie.

124
00:06:48,133 --> 00:06:49,367
Jade.

125
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,000
Jade, I'm sorry.

126
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:57,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:06:57,400 --> 00:07:00,000
Leon's gone because of me.

128
00:07:03,100 --> 00:07:05,000
It's not your fault, Kiko.

129
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,633
You didn't kill Leon.

130
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:12,433
He should've left me behind.

131
00:07:12,567 --> 00:07:14,900
He should've saved himself.

132
00:07:16,167 --> 00:07:17,733
[JADE] Kiko, stop.

133
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:19,800
Don't say that.

134
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:24,667
I know that if you were
in Leon's position,

135
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,900
you would've done
the same thing.

136
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:31,300
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

137
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:36,400
Until the end,
Leon proved that

138
00:07:36,533 --> 00:07:38,500
he is an honorable man.

139
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,733
He was the best son.

140
00:07:44,267 --> 00:07:47,100
He was also the best brother.

141
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:50,467
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

142
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:53,033
Him saving you...

143
00:07:53,933 --> 00:07:57,333
is proof that
he's a good person.

144
00:07:57,467 --> 00:08:02,167
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

145
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:04,500
Until the end...

146
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:09,133
he was thinking
of you and your siblings.

147
00:08:09,267 --> 00:08:16,100
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

148
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:20,933
Jade, I'm sorry.

149
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,867
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,433
I'm sorry you lost someone
so important to you.

151
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:32,533
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

152
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:34,700
I promise...

153
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:37,967
I promise I won't let
Leon's death be for nothing.

154
00:08:40,533 --> 00:08:42,200
[BREATH QUIVERS]

155
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,233
I appreciate it, Kiko.

156
00:08:44,367 --> 00:08:46,300
Thank you. [SNIFFLES]

157
00:08:46,433 --> 00:08:50,767
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

158
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:53,033
[INHALES, EXHALES HEAVILY]

159
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:55,467
I'm glad that
during Leon's final moments,

160
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:57,067
he wasn't alone.

161
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:02,233
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

162
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:06,533
Thank you for not giving up.

163
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:13,700
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

164
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:23,567
[RAPHIE] Welcome back, Sir Kiko.

165
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:27,033
Thank you, Raphie, Trixie.

166
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:29,833
- Ma, have you...
- [GIO] Come in, auntie.

167
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:31,700
Have you met them yet?

168
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:35,500
Uh, sir, Sari also said
to get well soon.

169
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:36,633
She's taking care
of her grandfather,

170
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:38,333
so she couldn't come today.

171
00:09:38,467 --> 00:09:39,967
Please tell her thank you.

172
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:41,700
[RAPHIE] I'll just prepare
some snacks for you.

173
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:44,167
- Excuse me.
- Ma, this is Trixie.

174
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:45,733
Martin's sister.

175
00:09:45,867 --> 00:09:47,033
- Hello.
- Hello, I'm Trixie.

176
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:48,233
Nice to meet you.

177
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:50,400
How about you, Kiko?
How are you?

178
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,633
How are you?

179
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,433
I'm back to being a strong man.

180
00:09:55,567 --> 00:09:58,967
I was supposed to be discharged
the other day, but...

181
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,800
- ...Gio wouldn't let me.
- Let it pass, Kiko.

182
00:10:01,967 --> 00:10:03,700
It's not every day
your brothers baby you.

183
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:05,367
Just let them.

184
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,400
Besides, it's better to
make sure you're really okay

185
00:10:07,533 --> 00:10:08,767
before leaving
the hospital, right?

186
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,567
[KIKO] I'm already strong.

187
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:11,900
I can't afford to be weak,

188
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:13,967
especially since Sandro
still hasn't been caught.

189
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:16,633
We still have work to do.

190
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:21,533
Son, I was just about
to tell your brothers this.

191
00:10:21,667 --> 00:10:24,400
But I want to take you
and Cheska home.

192
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:25,600
- Ma.
- [CHESKA] Ma?

193
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:29,000
Kiko, your life has already
been put in danger.

194
00:10:29,133 --> 00:10:29,833
[SIGHS]

195
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:34,200
As long as things aren't settled
at this hotel,

196
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:35,767
I'm not leaving my brothers.

197
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:38,167
[CHESKA] What?

198
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:39,300
Don't do this, Ma.

199
00:10:39,433 --> 00:10:40,133
No!

200
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:45,300
[SIGHS]

201
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:47,500
[GIO] We'll leave you for now.

202
00:10:47,633 --> 00:10:49,233
- Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

203
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,733
[CHESKA] Ma...

204
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:57,067
- You're going home, Cheska.
- No...

205
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,767
Ma, if Kiko is staying here,
then I'm staying here too.

206
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:04,167
Cheska, you're going home.

207
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:06,700
Your brother and I
will stay here.

208
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,300
- [CHESKA] Ma?!
- Ma!

209
00:11:08,467 --> 00:11:11,367
[GEORGIA] I will act as
a mother this time.

210
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:12,833
You're going home,

211
00:11:12,967 --> 00:11:14,833
and I'll stay here
with your brother

212
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:16,700
until things settle down.

213
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:18,367
Do we understand each other?

214
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:21,133
[EXHALES]
Ma, come on. Please?

215
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,467
[GEORGIA] Dear...

216
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:28,433
I've been letting you have your
way for a long time, haven't I?

217
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:32,700
This time, please let me
have my way.

218
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:35,467
- Ma, please.
- No!

219
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:39,300
[SIGHS]

220
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:41,900
Martin, I want to be here
for my friends.

221
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:44,067
What happened the last time
you disobeyed me?

222
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:50,067
[GIO] Trixie,
listen to your brother.

223
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:52,933
He's just worried about you.

224
00:11:54,567 --> 00:11:56,333
This place isn't safe.

225
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:00,000
Then why are you staying?

226
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:02,367
Because this is our home.

227
00:12:04,367 --> 00:12:07,000
Our father left this for us
to protect and take care of.

228
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,867
That's why
we're fighting for it.

229
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:15,933
I know you're worried about me.

230
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:19,033
You're worried
about your friends here.

231
00:12:19,933 --> 00:12:21,900
But this is the
right thing to do.

232
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,333
Go on.

233
00:12:27,467 --> 00:12:30,267
Pack your things
so you can leave anytime.

234
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:37,233
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

235
00:12:44,733 --> 00:12:45,900
[SIGHS]

236
00:12:50,367 --> 00:12:52,033
I hope all of this
gets resolved soon.

237
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:55,867
So we won't have
to send home people

238
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,200
who just want
to stay by our side.

239
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,500
Not "I hope"...

240
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:04,967
...but we need to.

241
00:13:05,100 --> 00:13:12,200
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,567
Jade, where's Luna?

243
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,033
She's still in the storage room.
She's cleaning.

244
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:21,533
There's something
wrong with her.

245
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:24,933
I know.

246
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:27,833
I just keep thinking
this is her way of grieving.

247
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:32,167
That's the book you and Kiko
were trying to figure out.

248
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:34,767
Yes.

249
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:36,267
You're planning something.

250
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,400
You wouldn't bring that out
for no reason.

251
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:43,633
I'm continuing the search
for the treasure.

252
00:13:43,767 --> 00:13:44,833
Are you serious?

253
00:13:44,967 --> 00:13:46,267
[JADE] Yes.

254
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:49,300
We need to find
the last map, Justin.

255
00:13:49,433 --> 00:13:51,200
That Sandro is a threat
to our lives

256
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:53,367
because he wants to get
all the clues.

257
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,600
That's why we need to find
the treasure before he does,

258
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:57,967
because if it ends up with him--

259
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,567
He'll get rid of all of us.

260
00:14:01,033 --> 00:14:02,867
Including the people
at Hotel 88.

261
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,733
Just so he can take the hotel
and the treasure for himself.

262
00:14:07,867 --> 00:14:14,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:27,733
Fine.

264
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,333
Then we'll look for it together.

265
00:14:29,467 --> 00:14:30,400
No.

266
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,633
With everything
that's happening,

267
00:14:34,767 --> 00:14:35,767
you can't go by yourself.

268
00:14:39,233 --> 00:14:42,033
I think they'll trust me more
if I go there alone.

269
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:44,833
And besides,
I'll be safe there.

270
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,400
I go there all the time,
remember?

271
00:14:47,533 --> 00:14:48,633
What if Mom finds out?

272
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:52,033
Don't tell them anything.

273
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:55,133
[EXHALES]

274
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:58,033
This is not a good idea, Jade.

275
00:14:58,167 --> 00:15:00,333
Good idea or not, I'm going.

276
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,267
Would you rather know
where I'm going,

277
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:05,433
or be completely clueless
like Luna and the others?

278
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:07,500
[SIGHS]

279
00:15:08,367 --> 00:15:09,433
Alright.

280
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:12,100
I'll leave now
while it's still early.

281
00:15:13,933 --> 00:15:15,067
Fine.

282
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,533
I'll handle Mom.

283
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,000
But, Jade...

284
00:15:20,133 --> 00:15:22,400
Please call me.

285
00:15:22,533 --> 00:15:25,033
I always have my phone with me.
I'll answer anytime.

286
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:29,333
I will be fine, Justin.

287
00:15:30,467 --> 00:15:31,767
But okay.

288
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:33,133
If something goes wrong,

289
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:35,233
you'll be the first person
I call.

290
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,300
You've changed, Jade.

291
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:43,300
I've never seen you
this brave before.

292
00:15:44,567 --> 00:15:47,100
And I don't know if that's
a good thing or a bad thing.

293
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:50,667
Luna and I are the same, Justin.

294
00:15:52,967 --> 00:15:54,733
I don't want to lose
anyone else.

295
00:15:56,133 --> 00:15:57,733
So what I'm doing...

296
00:15:57,867 --> 00:16:00,567
is my way of protecting
our family.

297
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:07,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

298
00:16:12,167 --> 00:16:16,033
[KEYBOARD CLANKING]

299
00:16:16,167 --> 00:16:23,467
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

300
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:26,800
[SANDRO]<i> They thought
</i> they could outsmart me.

301
00:16:26,933 --> 00:16:28,433
<i> I'll be the one watching you</i>

302
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:30,767
<i>through the cameras
you installed.</i>

303
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:37,733
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

304
00:16:43,367 --> 00:16:46,500
<i>And once I track down
where the treasure is...</i>

305
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:48,433
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

306
00:16:49,833 --> 00:16:51,133
<i> Boom!</i>

307
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:56,500
<i>Anyone who gets in my way
will die.</i>

308
00:16:57,467 --> 00:17:00,167
<i>I'll take you all down,
one by one!</i>

309
00:17:07,233 --> 00:17:08,433
[TRIXIE] I'm going to miss this.

310
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:10,833
You mean the view?

311
00:17:12,033 --> 00:17:13,067
No.

312
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,900
I mean, us hanging out
like this.

313
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:18,700
Come on.

314
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:21,500
We can still keep in touch.

315
00:17:22,533 --> 00:17:24,033
And Justin...

316
00:17:26,033 --> 00:17:26,933
Hey.

317
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:28,833
How are you holding up?

318
00:17:29,467 --> 00:17:31,400
I'm sorry.

319
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:35,733
We haven't been able
to spend time with you lately.

320
00:17:36,867 --> 00:17:39,667
We didn't even get to say
goodbye to Leon properly.

321
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:41,633
It's fine.

322
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,767
I should be the one apologizing.

323
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:50,533
Mom drove your brothers away.

324
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:53,833
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

325
00:17:53,967 --> 00:17:54,967
It's okay.

326
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:57,800
Our brothers understand.

327
00:17:59,533 --> 00:18:01,000
But how are you doing?

328
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,900
Honestly...

329
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,533
I still can't believe
my brother is gone.

330
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:14,067
I've told you that.

331
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:19,400
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

332
00:18:19,533 --> 00:18:20,733
Justin...

333
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,800
we're here for you, okay?

334
00:18:25,733 --> 00:18:29,133
Whenever you don't want
to burden your family,

335
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:31,900
you can lean on me and Cheska.

336
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:34,533
Right, Ches?

337
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:38,767
Of course.

338
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,167
I owe Leon my brother's life.

339
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,367
Thank you.

340
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:52,333
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

341
00:18:52,467 --> 00:18:54,200
But it can't always
be like that.

342
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:57,133
You'll both be going home soon.

343
00:19:03,067 --> 00:19:04,233
Don't get me wrong.

344
00:19:05,767 --> 00:19:07,233
That's what I want too.

345
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:10,433
For you to go home and be safe.

346
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:14,567
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

347
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:16,667
But that doesn't make it
any less sad.

348
00:19:21,633 --> 00:19:23,000
[FRIDA] What are you doing here?

349
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,500
I just want to talk to Luna.

350
00:19:25,633 --> 00:19:26,833
Didn't I tell you

351
00:19:26,967 --> 00:19:29,767
I don't want to see you
and your brothers in my house?

352
00:19:29,933 --> 00:19:31,067
She's not okay, is she?

353
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,500
I know she's having
a hard time right now.

354
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:33,467
- No!
- Luna!

355
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:34,433
Just leave!

356
00:19:34,567 --> 00:19:39,000
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

357
00:19:39,133 --> 00:19:40,000
Luna!

358
00:19:42,433 --> 00:19:43,867
[LUNA] How did you get in here?

359
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,567
[GIO] That's not important.

360
00:19:47,033 --> 00:19:50,233
[LUNA] Gio, I'm busy.
I don't have time.

361
00:19:50,367 --> 00:19:52,767
I just finished sorting through
Leon's things in the warehouse.

362
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,633
And I'll ask Jade to paint
Leon's portrait.

363
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:56,100
She can definitely do it.

364
00:19:56,233 --> 00:19:57,400
As for the warehouse--

365
00:19:57,533 --> 00:19:59,533
Luna, can you stop for a second?
Let's talk!

366
00:19:59,667 --> 00:20:05,833
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:08,833
[GIO] Cry if you want to cry.

368
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:11,267
If you want
to break something...

369
00:20:12,267 --> 00:20:13,300
Here. Do it.

370
00:20:13,433 --> 00:20:14,633
Stop it!

371
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:18,467
Are you angry at me?

372
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,667
At my brothers?! At us?!

373
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:22,400
- Then take it out on me!
- What are you doing?!

374
00:20:22,533 --> 00:20:24,100
- Take it out on me!
- Gio, stop it!

375
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:25,800
Let it out!

376
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,600
No matter how many times
you clean your house,

377
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:29,300
if you keep bottling up
your emotions,

378
00:20:29,433 --> 00:20:31,133
then nothing's going to change!

379
00:20:31,267 --> 00:20:32,100
So, go ahead!

380
00:20:32,867 --> 00:20:35,367
Do whatever you want! Do it!

381
00:20:35,533 --> 00:20:37,200
- Whatever I want?
- Whatever you want!

382
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:39,233
- Really?!
- Yes!

383
00:20:40,067 --> 00:20:41,500
I've had enough!

384
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:43,200
I can't do this anymore, Gio!

385
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:45,100
I don't want anyone else to die!

386
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:47,100
I don't want people to leave
and never come back!

387
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:47,833
Okay!

388
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,600
I'm sick of it! I'm sick of it!

389
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:56,500
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

390
00:20:56,633 --> 00:20:58,633
- [SNIFFLES]
- Luna, I'm right here.

391
00:21:00,533 --> 00:21:02,033
I won't run away from you.

392
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:04,833
I'm not going to disappear
from your life.

393
00:21:12,967 --> 00:21:16,833
Before I forget,
I have something to give you.

394
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:22,600
[JUSTIN] Cheska.

395
00:21:22,733 --> 00:21:24,267
This map again?

396
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:26,700
This is exactly what got
your brother into trouble.

397
00:21:26,833 --> 00:21:28,833
Kiko doesn't know I took it.

398
00:21:28,967 --> 00:21:30,633
He's definitely going
to be mad at you.

399
00:21:30,767 --> 00:21:32,067
This is the last time anyway.

400
00:21:32,767 --> 00:21:34,233
We're leaving soon.

401
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:37,767
Remember that place
that's marked on the map?

402
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:39,267
Yes, that's where we went to.

403
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:43,033
I feel like we went
to the wrong place.

404
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:44,100
Huh?

405
00:21:44,833 --> 00:21:46,100
[CHESKA] I just...

406
00:21:46,233 --> 00:21:49,400
I don't know
how to explain it, but...

407
00:21:50,933 --> 00:21:53,100
I feel like we still have
an unfinished business.

408
00:21:53,233 --> 00:21:54,200
Enough of this.

409
00:21:55,267 --> 00:21:57,433
I'll keep it.

410
00:21:57,567 --> 00:21:58,733
What if they look for it?

411
00:21:58,867 --> 00:22:01,567
[JUSTIN] Then I'll give it
to them if they look for it.

412
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:05,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

413
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:13,900
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

414
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:15,300
Jade.

415
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:19,267
[JADE] I asked to meet
because I need your help.

416
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:22,067
Okay.

417
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:24,733
Apparently, this community
you support

418
00:22:24,867 --> 00:22:27,033
used to be called
Oscalara.

419
00:22:27,967 --> 00:22:29,467
Oscalara? Isn't that
what we found--

420
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,467
[JADE] At the church.

421
00:22:31,633 --> 00:22:32,967
There is an elder
who lives here

422
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:36,233
who knows about the clues
we saw in the book.

423
00:22:37,067 --> 00:22:38,733
But she doesn't want
to talk to us.

424
00:22:39,467 --> 00:22:41,567
She said she'll only speak
to an Arellano.

425
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:43,433
She only trusts your family.

426
00:22:44,833 --> 00:22:46,333
So I need you.

427
00:22:46,467 --> 00:22:53,200
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

428
00:22:56,800 --> 00:23:00,767
[EXHALES DEEPLY]
All done.

429
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:02,100
Let's go?

430
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,233
Wait.

431
00:23:07,133 --> 00:23:11,133
You see, Trixie,
I remembered something.

432
00:23:11,267 --> 00:23:14,400
I've noticed a steel railing
in the woods.

433
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:15,867
Steel railing?

434
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,400
And so?

435
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:18,867
Don't you find it weird?

436
00:23:19,767 --> 00:23:22,700
Why would there be steel railing
deep in the forest?

437
00:23:22,867 --> 00:23:25,667
Cheska, I don't know, okay?

438
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,900
[GRUNTS]

439
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:29,367
What if it's a path used
by the killer,

440
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:30,667
don't you think?

441
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:35,267
Then, what? You want to film it
for your content?

442
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,267
Huh?

443
00:23:36,967 --> 00:23:38,533
I'm not posting anything.

444
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:41,433
But you're still keeping them so
you can post them in the future.

445
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:44,433
[CHESKA] Trixie...

446
00:23:44,567 --> 00:23:47,733
Cheska, come on. Our brothers
are telling us to leave,

447
00:23:47,867 --> 00:23:49,333
and you're still thinking
about that?

448
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:53,467
Trixie, please.

449
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:56,533
This will be the last time.

450
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:59,000
[CHESKA] If we go there

451
00:23:59,767 --> 00:24:00,767
and we don't find anything...

452
00:24:01,867 --> 00:24:04,033
then let's go back home.

453
00:24:05,833 --> 00:24:08,000
[SIGHS] Goodness, Cheska.

454
00:24:08,133 --> 00:24:09,233
[CLICKS TONGUE]

455
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:12,067
[CHESKA] Trixie, please.

456
00:24:12,967 --> 00:24:14,400
Just think of it...

457
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:18,567
as our last attempt
to help them.

458
00:24:20,233 --> 00:24:21,567
For our brothers.

459
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:23,867
Who knows?

460
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,500
What if we find something?

461
00:24:25,633 --> 00:24:29,967
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

462
00:24:30,133 --> 00:24:31,500
Fine.

463
00:24:31,633 --> 00:24:33,533
But this is the last one,
got it?

464
00:24:33,667 --> 00:24:34,733
No more next time.

465
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:36,800
Thank you.

466
00:24:37,867 --> 00:24:39,067
Thank you.

467
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:42,133
This is the last one, I promise.

468
00:24:44,367 --> 00:24:47,500
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

469
00:24:47,633 --> 00:24:49,600
[TRIXIE] Where's the railing
you're talking about?

470
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,167
I can't see it.

471
00:24:52,300 --> 00:24:54,333
It's probably over there.

472
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:02,800
Trixie, just say it.

473
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:05,767
What? Did I do anything?
Are you mad?

474
00:25:07,067 --> 00:25:08,567
I'm annoyed.

475
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:10,133
By what?

476
00:25:10,267 --> 00:25:11,900
Because you made me
go with you.

477
00:25:12,033 --> 00:25:13,600
Martin is going to scold me.

478
00:25:13,733 --> 00:25:14,800
Again.

479
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:17,267
Fine.

480
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:19,133
If you really don't want
to do this,

481
00:25:19,933 --> 00:25:21,133
just go home.

482
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:23,833
Why are you so slow?

483
00:25:25,867 --> 00:25:27,100
We just got here.

484
00:25:27,233 --> 00:25:29,200
And I told you I can't find it.

485
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:33,100
[SIGHS] Cheska, there's
no point in what we're doing.

486
00:25:33,233 --> 00:25:35,633
Come on. Let's just
go back to the hotel.

487
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:38,733
- Oh!
- Oh!

488
00:25:38,867 --> 00:25:40,567
- Trixie, run!
- [SCREAMING]

489
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:42,800
[SCREAMING, COUGHS]

490
00:25:42,933 --> 00:25:45,433
Let me go! [SCREAMING]

491
00:25:46,700 --> 00:25:49,033
[PANTS, SCREAMS]

492
00:25:49,167 --> 00:25:50,833
- No! Please don't!
- [BLOW LANDS]

493
00:25:50,967 --> 00:25:57,867
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

494
00:25:59,267 --> 00:26:01,167
<i> They're not at the Almazan's.</i>

495
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:02,867
<i>If they're not there
and they're not here,</i>

496
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,000
then where's Trixie and Cheska?

497
00:26:04,133 --> 00:26:05,400
<i> Are they missing?</i>

498
00:26:07,333 --> 00:26:08,800
<i> Are they missing?!</i>

499
00:26:08,967 --> 00:26:09,867
<i> Yes.</i>

500
00:26:11,033 --> 00:26:12,200
<i> Ma.</i>

501
00:26:12,333 --> 00:26:13,233
<i> Tamara...</i>

502
00:26:13,367 --> 00:26:14,633
<i>You shouldn't have
come back here.</i>

503
00:26:14,767 --> 00:26:17,300
<i>You said you only trust
the Arellanos.</i>

504
00:26:18,667 --> 00:26:20,067
<i> Trixie!</i>

505
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,367
<i> Trixie!</i>

506
00:26:22,767 --> 00:26:24,367
<i> Help!</i> [CRIES]

507
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:26,000
<i> Help--</i> [SCREAMING]

508
00:26:26,133 --> 00:26:27,300
<i> Help!</i>
